{
  "stem": "8679.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We didn't get food.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We didn't get water.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They put a container in that cattle car to relieve ourselves.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We were men, women.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "In ours were still two children.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "There were very few.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "In ours was two children-- two little girls that I remembered.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Every so often, the guard-- the train came to a stop, a guard opened the door, and one of us emptied the container and put it back.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Now, I don't know if anyone can understand what it meant to relieve yourself in front of men, women, and children.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was the greatest indignity that we have encountered so far.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Like I said before, wearing the star of David, the badge of shame, like the Nazis referred to, didn't bother me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But this bothered me, and it bothered every one of us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Where was our dignity?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What did they do to us?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remember when they said that we are sub-humans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Maybe that's how you treat sub-humans.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They don't deserve to be treated like human beings.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The journey lasted five days.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had not the faintest idea where we are going-- nothing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We arrived at Auschwitz-Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's together on the station.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I had never known, and nobody knew, what Auschwitz meant, because nobody had come back from Auschwitz to tell us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "A guard-- before a guard opened the door, or right as he opened it, actually, we have seen men, terribly like skeletons, in that camp, in their striped uniforms and little funny caps, striped also, on their heads.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a Jewish prisoner, inmate of Auschwitz, who opened the door and helped us out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I hear him like I would hear him today.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He said, there is gas here.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was numb by that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I was totally numb.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
